reviews.review: Absolutely loved it! Perfect conclusion to the Skywalker saga.

The movie got some amazing parts and really bad ones. Some scenes have that really wanted nostalgia feeling of old-time great sw, others are more like scenes from Harry Potter. The end of the movie is plain, it feels like JJ Abrams cant make those amazing final battles as we have seen in Revenge of the Sith or in Return of the Jedi. However, I think it can be considered as the best of the current trilogy which after those two is a huge relief.
Solo olvidaria la parte tipo romeo y julieta

I don't understand why anyone wouldn't like this movie. It has everything...action, adventure, comedy, friendship, amazing special effects, and even a little romance. What a satisfying way to wrap up this monumental story. I can't wait to see it again!

JJ Abrams made the best possible ending considering the Rian Johnson disaster of Episode 8. Key script failure: Annhilation of the prophecy of "the chosen one" where Anakin is finally no use to restoring balance in the force. Second failure, the ending Ben Solo scene which make absolutely no sense.
For everything else than those two script failure, this is the best Star Wars ever in rhythm and realisation-wise. You were so close to the perfect master-chief and you made the best of the Rian Johnson mess from the last episode.
The film is absolutely great, a good ending for the saga. If the force awakens seemed too familiar, and last Jedi was too radical, then the rise of Skywalker is that happy middle ground
i enjoyed it!!! way to redeem from Last Jedi. wrapped up 6he story nicely!!!! couple things i didn't like but still a must see and to see it again!!!

A Star Wars movie shot and edited like a heist movie , the movie moves fast and yet it was a slow burn. Fantastic finale to a decade long ride , not perfect, but for the hype, controversy, and legacy ..it hit the right notes .

The levels of BS plot devices were pretty annoying (new force powers revealed like they're going out of style, evil empires with an endless supply of newly discovered superweapons). On top of that, the final resolution was pretty boring and unfulfilling. It would have been much more interesting to see an interesting turn being taken, instead of 'Good guys win, bad guys are all conveniently neutralized'.
Great way to end the franchise!
